The paper deals with the task of robust non-linear estimation, which is a common problem in machine learning and computer vision. The use of Reproducing Kernel Hilbert Space (RKHS) and kernel regression matrix suggests that the paper belongs to the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The application of the proposed method to image denoising indicates that the paper may also belong to the category of cs.CV (Computer Vision). The use of sparse modeling arguments and the Orthogonal Matching Pursuit (OMP) algorithm suggests that the paper may belong to the category of cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) or cs.IT (Information Theory). Finally, the consideration of outliers and the proposed robust estimation framework suggest that the paper may also belong to the category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
